title.narrative: IR 1.4: HEALTH & NUTRITION

description.narrative: IR 1.4: Relevant Core Commitments on Health & Nutrition are met in all humanitarian settings, which contributes to Child Health, Health And Emergencies, Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: PCR1. National institutions provide improved health and neonatal care services and quality early childhood care with a focus on disadvantaged groups.

title.narrative: IR 1.4: Relevant Core Commitments on Health & Nutrition are met in all humanitarian settings
Number of Children <5 and Pregnant Lactating Women receiving multi-micronutrient supplementation
Number of women having access to Infant and Young Child Feeding Services
Number (and%) of new borns receiving health kits in target population

actual.value: 2014:3,045 Newborn Baby health kits(together with 3,015 mother health kits) were distributed to the new born babies & mothers in Za'atari and Azraq camps. The programme reached only 50% target due to shortage of fund

title.narrative: In-depth nutrition assessment report providing the detailed malnutrition information on children (6-59 months) and PLWs

actual.value: 2014:In-depth nutrition assessment report is finalized and waiting for endorsement by Ministry of Health

title.narrative: Number (and %) of children (boys and girls) vaccinated against Polio

actual.value: 2014:Over 1 million children under the age of five (113 per cent) in each National Immunisation Days (NID) and 200,000 in each Sub-national Immunisation Days (SNID) with two drops of oral polio vaccination

title.narrative: Number (and % of target) of MOH doctors & nurses trained on IMCI

actual.value: 2014:72 health providers were trained on 9-days clinical management training on Integrated Management of Childhood Illness in northern governorates and 36 health providers in Za'atari camp. Target was not achieved due to insufficient funding

title.narrative: Number of ORT corners providing early identification & treatment for diarrhea

actual.value: 2014:8 additional Oral Rehydration Therapy corners (total 16) established in three camps and providing Oral Rehydration Salt for diarrhoea treatment
